President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate Mark A. Robbins as a member of the Merit Systems Protection Board. Robbins currently serves as the General Counsel of the U.S. Election Assistance Commission and has experience in certifying election systems and maintaining information on best practices for conducting elections. He has also served in various roles in the State Department, White House, and Office of Personnel Management. Robbins holds a B.A. and J.D. from George Washington University.

Additionally, President Obama intends to nominate Tony Hammond as a Commissioner of the Postal Regulatory Commission. Hammond previously served on the Postal Regulatory Commission and its predecessor agency, the Postal Rate Commission, for almost a decade. He has experience in consulting and direct marketing and also worked on the staff of a Congressman. Hammond holds a B.S. from Missouri State University.